Ekiti State Governor Kayode Fayemi has stressed the need for the people to ensure the All Progressives Congress (APC) forms the next government come June 18. Fayemi said his administration has laid a good solid foundation that requires a purpose-driven and intelligent person like the APC governorship candidate, Biodun Oyebanji, to consolidate on in the overall interest of the citizenry. He addressed reporters after inspecting the on-going terminal buildings, runway and other sections of the Ekiti airport in Ado-Ekiti.   Gunmen set police station, vehicles ablaze in Anambra     Fayose’s ally, others join APC     APC insists on screening Jonathan, Emefiele, Ngige   The governor was on a tour of projects within the state capital.The governor appealed to the electorate to vote massively for APC to ensure continuity of development initiatives, and avert a reverse in the laudable gains of the current administration. According to him, the APC-led administration has been beneficial, in no small measure, to the people than the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) government in the state. He said what ‘Ekiti needs now is continuity and not change of government’. Governor Fayemi expressed delight at the pace and quality of work at the Ekiti cargo airport, model colleges and other ongoing legacy projects, with an assurance to hand over the projects before the expiration of his administration in October.